gomodel:SYNGO_5286  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 9a,b: immunofluorescence imaging of cultured hippocampal neurons showed overexpressed myosin IXb (MYO9B) showed enrichment in spine heads 1.6 times that of mCherry.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Briefly, the hippocampi of embryonal day 17 Wistar rat fetuses of either sex were dissected and brains obtained.\"\n\n\"mCherry-tagged SWAP-70, myosin IXb, and myosin IIb constructs were kind gifts from Martin Bähler (SWAP-70 and Myosin IXb, WestfalianWilhelms-University, Münster, Germany) and Alan Rick Horwitz (MHCIIb, University of Virginia, USA).\"\n\nHuman protein was overexpressed, also for mutated sequence (Figure 8)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5286" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

